Features
        ğŸ” 3D Model of Everest: A detailed, interactive 3D model of Mount Everest.

        ğŸ• Interactive Markers: Clickable markers representing Base Camp, Camp 1, Camp 2, Camp 3, Camp 4, and the Summit, each with detailed descriptions.

        ğŸ’¬ Info Popups: Hover and click to display information about each camp and the summit.

        ğŸŒ Custom UI: A user interface to control elements like wireframe visibility, gradient adjustments, and more.

        ğŸ–¥ Best viewed on Desktop: This project is designed primarily for desktop and isn't optimized for mobile devices yet.


Technologies Used
        Three.js: 3D rendering and animation for the Everest model.
        GLTFLoader: Used to load the 3D models of Everest.
        GSAP: For smooth animations and transitions.
        dat.GUI: For real-time controls over visual elements like colors and wireframes.
        HTML/CSS: Structure and styling of the website.
        JavaScript: For dynamic interactions and 3D rendering.
        Blender: For 3d obj.
Known Issues
        ğŸ“± Mobile Compatibility: The website is not fully optimized for mobile devices yet. It's recommended to view the website on a desktop for the best experience.
        â³ Loading Time: Depending on your internet connection, the 3D model might take a few seconds to load.
